1
00:00:03,003 --> 00:00:05,797
(Towa) Long time no see, Dora

2
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:08,383
I came to ask for representation in court.

3
00:00:08,466 --> 00:00:09,592
(Kotaro) The person who complained was⸺

4
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:12,095
Ryoma Tsuge, member of the House of Representatives

5
00:00:12,178 --> 00:00:13,471
(Usagiha) My article is⸺

6
00:00:13,555 --> 00:00:16,266
I want to claim that I wasn't wrong.

7
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:19,394
(Tatsumi) Usa-chan’s aim is to buy time.

8
00:00:19,477 --> 00:00:21,104
(Tatsumi) Aiming for a draw from the beginning...

9
00:00:21,187 --> 00:00:22,689
Doesn't look like Toba-chan

10
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:24,607
This is all I have now

11
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:27,861
(Tatsumi) How did you manage to write an article about specific numbers?

12
00:00:27,944 --> 00:00:29,529
I was recording it, so I'll listen to it again later⸺

13
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:31,072
Does that mean you made it into an article?

14
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:32,365
(Tsuge) This is not a misunderstanding.

15
00:00:32,449 --> 00:00:34,784
(Tatsumi) Did something happen to Kotaro-sensei?

16
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:36,161
(Toshie) He was arrested.

17
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:37,787
Arrested! ?

18
00:00:44,627 --> 00:00:45,962
thank you

19
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:55,930
I'm glad he was acquitted.

20
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:03,104
Because the act was recognized as minor, he was not sent to the prosecutor's office.

21
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:06,274
(Rie) That's why that reporter named Jinno called Mr. Torataro⸺

22
00:01:06,357 --> 00:01:07,901
It doesn't change the fact that you fell into the trap.

23
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:09,444
Tell the police about that?

24
00:01:10,278 --> 00:01:14,699
Of course I talked about it, but Jinno's smartphone is probably a cell phone.

25
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:17,869
The first email I received was also a free account⸺

26
00:01:17,952 --> 00:01:20,413
It might be difficult to prove it's a trap

27
00:01:21,247 --> 00:01:24,918
(Rie) I immediately received a fax from the Central Bar Association.

28
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:26,002
(Torataro) Huh?

29
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:30,090
It appears that Representative Tsuge has filed a disciplinary request with the bar association.

30
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:33,885
(Torataro) “Suspicion of violating Article 52 of the Basic Rules for Lawyer Duties”?

31
00:01:33,968 --> 00:01:36,054
(Rie) From the perspective of lawyer ethics, to the other party himself⸺

32
00:01:36,137 --> 00:01:38,681
There should be no direct contact.

33
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:41,226
...But Torataro-sensei was only summoned by Kamino.

34
00:01:41,309 --> 00:01:45,355
(Rie) I think the problem is that videos like this are being circulated.

35
00:01:47,524 --> 00:01:48,733
(Torataro) Please let go!

36
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:51,820
(Officer) If you don't calm down, I'll arrest you for obstructing official duties.

37
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:54,447
(Torataro) It's some kind of misunderstanding. I'm a lawyer...

38
00:01:57,158 --> 00:01:59,077
(Officer) Hey, hurry up and get on!

39
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:03,331
I never thought this video was the purpose of me from the beginning...

40
00:02:04,082 --> 00:02:06,876
(Tatsumi) This is all slander...

41
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,087
(Rie) There is also a summary site, but it's better not to look at it anymore.

42
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:12,715
Kotaro Sensei's photo, name, and academic background are all exposed.

43
00:02:17,011 --> 00:02:18,555
It's all my fault (sound of door opening)

44
00:02:18,638 --> 00:02:22,642
(Usagiba) No, it's my fault.

45
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:24,602
Usaha-chan

46
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:28,147
(Usaha) It's because I got Ryumi and Kotaro-sensei involved.

47
00:02:28,231 --> 00:02:29,941
This is what happened

48
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:33,069
I'm really sorry

49
00:02:33,152 --> 00:02:34,112
no…

50
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:40,326
(phone ringtone)

51
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:43,288
Yes, if you have a complaint, come to Ayuda Law Office...

52
00:02:43,955 --> 00:02:46,082
Ah, excuse me

53
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:50,169
Yes, offer of reconciliation?

54
00:02:51,921 --> 00:02:53,506
Is it from Representative Tsuge's side?

55
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:58,970
A proposal for reconciliation at this timing?

56
00:03:00,096 --> 00:03:03,224
I think it's the same as telling him to surrender.

57
00:03:08,104 --> 00:03:10,565
(Nakazumi) This is a settlement proposal.

58
00:03:19,824 --> 00:03:22,035
Tokyo TV news program⸺

59
00:03:22,118 --> 00:03:24,746
I appeared and admitted that the article was fabricated⸺

60
00:03:24,829 --> 00:03:28,374
Apology is a condition for reconciliation

61
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:31,753
(Rie) To be frank, the content is humiliating.

62
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:34,339
One thing I'm curious about...

63
00:03:34,422 --> 00:03:37,967
(Rie) “All interview materials must be destroyed”

64
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:40,011
 (Nakazumi) I don't have time either, so⸺

65
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:42,096
Please reply if possible...

66
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:48,728
I won't drink under these conditions

67
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:57,153
(Rabbitha) What do you mean?

68
00:03:57,236 --> 00:04:00,990
If I pick a fight with Congressman Tsuge now, I'm sure he'll call me a dora⸺

69
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:03,034
I don't understand that people are paying attention to me! ?

70
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:05,495
That's why it's definitely no good if you live under such conditions.

71
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:13,378
There's a recording, right?

72
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:22,720
The bad thing about Ukeba-chan, the impregnable Uke, is⸺

73
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:26,099
Trying to keep everything to yourself

74
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:29,519
And I'm sure it's not just for myself⸺

75
00:04:29,602 --> 00:04:30,979
for someone

76
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:36,067
I can't fight unless you teach me that.

77
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,533
Please dismiss the agent

78
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:45,410
Huh?

79
00:04:55,169 --> 00:04:57,755
Will you disappear again without saying anything?

80
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:01,134
(sound of sliding door opening)

81
00:05:06,848 --> 00:05:11,060
I want to face Toba-chan

82
00:05:13,688 --> 00:05:14,772
that's why…

83
00:05:18,484 --> 00:05:20,486
Point at me

84
00:05:28,453 --> 00:05:30,455
♪～

85
00:05:40,548 --> 00:05:42,550
～♪

86
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:46,387
(Torataro) Leave it behind...

87
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:48,306
- (Game clock voice) Hello - (Torataro) Oh!

88
00:05:48,389 --> 00:05:51,559
Hello, please

89
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:53,978
(game clock audio) Please set the rules

90
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:57,190
(Tatsuo) How did this happen?

91
00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:02,195
If you say so, it just happens.

92
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:09,619
(Kasumi) I feel like I understand somehow.

93
00:06:11,496 --> 00:06:15,666
With those two, there is no need to exchange words at length⸺

94
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:21,881
It would be much more refreshing to talk through the pieces.

95
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:25,301
I'm ready

96
00:06:35,019 --> 00:06:37,355
(Rie) The time limit is 90 minutes.

97
00:06:37,438 --> 00:06:41,192
After 90 minutes, it will be 1 minute shogi.

98
00:06:41,275 --> 00:06:43,152
The first move and the second move are swing pieces...

99
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:44,445
(2 people) No.

100
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:45,363
I'm the first one

101
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:47,365
I'll take the next turn, please.

102
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:53,413
As long as you both agree, that's fine.

103
00:06:54,956 --> 00:06:57,166
(2 people) Thank you very much.

104
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:58,793
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

105
00:07:05,758 --> 00:07:06,592
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

106
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:10,304
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

107
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:14,308
In that game too, Toba-chan was the first player.

108
00:07:15,476 --> 00:07:16,269
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

109
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:18,229
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

110
00:07:18,312 --> 00:07:19,856
(Sound of pointing to pieces) (Sound of pressing the game clock)

111
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:28,239
Anaguma vs. Shikenbisha This is the same

112
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:38,207
In the early stages, Tatsumi's offensive pieces are set up.

113
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:41,961
Toba-chan's counterattack against this

114
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:48,259
No doubt, it's the same as the game three and a half years ago.

115
00:07:49,051 --> 00:07:51,554
I can't believe it's the same game...

116
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:57,727
That Sandan League Game 17

117
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:07,153
(Sound of pointing to pieces) (Sound of pressing the game clock)

118
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:16,871
First move 3-money, different move for the first time

119
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:20,750
(Sound of pressing the game clock)

120
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:24,337
I've always wanted to hear it

121
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:38,392
The last game of shogi life

122
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:43,189
Also, if I lose to Ryumi, I'll attack her even more⸺

123
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:45,274
I wanted to be completely stuffed.

124
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:49,612
Just like⸺

125
00:08:49,695 --> 00:08:53,699
He kept pointing a hand that seemed to break my heart

126
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:04,543
In the end, they didn't even let me make the shape⸺

127
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:05,878
It was a miserable loss

128
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:13,010
Why are you doing that?

129
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:19,600
Because...

130
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:28,192
(Sound of pointing to pieces) (Sound of pressing the game clock)

131
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:35,658
I wanted to keep pointing at Usa-chan for as long as possible.

132
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:48,921
When this one game is over, Toba-chan will be gone.

133
00:09:50,506 --> 00:09:56,512
The two of us always search for and study even the slightest bit of formidable moves⸺

134
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:59,849
Toba-chan, who was aiming for the top with me

135
00:10:02,518 --> 00:10:06,689
That's why I point, I point frantically...

136
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:10,109
As long as you keep pointing at it⸺

137
00:10:11,902 --> 00:10:14,614
Because we could be in that atmosphere together

138
00:10:15,823 --> 00:10:17,325
(sound pointing to pieces)

139
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:29,837
(Sound of pointing to pieces) (Sound of pressing the game clock)

140
00:10:56,572 --> 00:10:58,991
(Tatsuo) What happened?

141
00:11:00,493 --> 00:11:02,161
Sennichite

142
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:07,541
(Rie) The same situation appears four times, so it's a thousand days.

143
00:11:09,668 --> 00:11:13,839
...That means this game is a draw.

144
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:32,692
I can point again

145
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:38,531
(Tatsumi's crying)

146
00:11:40,324 --> 00:11:41,784
sorry

147
00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:51,794
I had no idea that Toba-chan would get hurt.

148
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:56,465
just…

149
00:11:58,717 --> 00:12:02,263
I wanted to keep pointing at it with Toba-chan.

150
00:12:11,939 --> 00:12:13,274
(Rabbitha) It's okay.

151
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:20,656
It's me

152
00:12:22,783 --> 00:12:24,410
I wanted to apologize

153
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:26,871
Huh?

154
00:12:29,457 --> 00:12:33,461
Even though I lost to Dora, I didn't even thank you.

155
00:12:34,545 --> 00:12:36,630
Without even saying “I’m here”⸺

156
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:39,592
He disappeared from that place.

157
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:42,178
I have to apologize for that

158
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:44,930
forever…

159
00:12:47,933 --> 00:12:49,351
that's why…

160
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:52,438
(Tatsumi) Toba-chan

161
00:12:55,524 --> 00:12:56,859
It's okay now

162
00:13:29,099 --> 00:13:33,062
I needed someone's help to get through the trial.

163
00:13:33,687 --> 00:13:38,943
And that's with the help of someone I can truly believe in.

164
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:43,030
(Rie) That's why you needed Dr. Ryumi's help.

165
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:47,618
(Usaha) I wanted to say something about the recorded data right away.

166
00:13:48,577 --> 00:13:54,250
But if something happens to Dora or Kotaro-sensei because of that...

167
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:59,672
When I thought that way, I couldn't say anything.

168
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:03,342
sorry

169
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:17,523
the trial continues

170
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:22,278
I won't accept any settlement

171
00:14:27,491 --> 00:14:28,367
(Recorded audio: Tsuge) Ah...

172
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:31,870
I'm not good at recording, so could you please stop?

173
00:14:34,623 --> 00:14:39,461
It's definitely a recording from the night of the interview.

174
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:44,967
The problem is about 20 minutes into the interview⸺

175
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:48,971
It happened when I was leaving that room.

176
00:14:50,055 --> 00:14:54,476
(Usaha) What policy would Representative Tsuge want to focus on the most?

177
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:56,937
(Tsuge) Ah~ First of all, let's talk about Japanese politics itself...

178
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:58,314
(mobile phone vibrator)

179
00:14:58,397 --> 00:15:00,107
Ah, excuse me for a moment

180
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:03,903
I have to contact you for one urgent matter.

181
00:15:03,986 --> 00:15:08,198
I'm sorry, but could you leave your seat for about 20 minutes?

182
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:13,996
Ah, I understand, please excuse me.

183
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:24,089
There is another room at the back of the office⸺

184
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:26,800
You can also enter and exit from the hallway.

185
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:31,722
Congressman Tsuge spoke with someone in that room...

186
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:33,682
Somebody?

187
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:36,852
(Tsuge) What kind of wind is it blowing?

188
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:39,980
Interview: Do you think you're worried about just having a girlfriend?

189
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:44,026
(Recorded audio: Naomi) There is something I would like the members to see.

190
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:45,444
This voice...

191
00:15:45,527 --> 00:15:49,823
(Naomi) Since Komaki wrote it, I think he is conveying the truth.

192
00:15:49,907 --> 00:15:54,787
This is Naomi Kurosu, my boss and the person at the desk.

193
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:59,041
(Naozane) Please let me ask you about this injustice.

194
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:01,794
(Tsuge) What is your goal?

195
00:16:01,877 --> 00:16:05,589
(Naozane) If it's true, I have a duty to report it.

196
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:08,801
(Tsuge) Huh... You idiot, give it to me.

197
00:16:08,884 --> 00:16:09,843
-(Naomi) Please stop.-(Tsuge) It's okay!

198
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:11,553
(Naomi) Let go!

199
00:16:13,263 --> 00:16:14,098
This is...

200
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:17,101
Kurosu desk goes to Representative Tsuge⸺

201
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:19,728
This is an exchange when I was on duty.

202
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:23,982
It's also about some big injustice.

203
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:28,404
Representative Tsuge is probably⸺

204
00:16:28,487 --> 00:16:31,281
You should be aware of the existence of this recording.

205
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:33,826
Therefore, as a condition of reconciliation⸺

206
00:16:33,909 --> 00:16:38,497
I think they have included the destruction of all interview materials.

207
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:40,749
(Rie) So, this trial is...

208
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:44,086
This is not to argue whether the article is fabricated or not.

209
00:16:44,169 --> 00:16:46,213
To contain this recording⸺

210
00:16:46,296 --> 00:16:48,841
Does that mean that Representative Tsuge forced him to wake up?

211
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:53,721
I also want to know more details⸺

212
00:16:53,804 --> 00:16:56,849
I heard from Mr. Kurosu.

213
00:16:56,932 --> 00:16:58,475
There is a recording

214
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:02,438
While I was away

215
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:04,440
Did you hear that?

216
00:17:04,523 --> 00:17:06,358
About Representative Tsuge⸺

217
00:17:06,442 --> 00:17:08,569
Please tell me what kind of material you are getting into.

218
00:17:08,652 --> 00:17:09,695
You don't need to know!

219
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:14,241
This is far more dangerous than you think.

220
00:17:14,324 --> 00:17:17,202
You may be in danger

221
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:22,207
This injustice must be exposed to the world.

222
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:24,501
But it takes time.

223
00:17:24,585 --> 00:17:28,464
Until then, let's pretend there was no recording of you.

224
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:33,218
(Tatsumi) That's why I kept the recording data hidden⸺

225
00:17:33,302 --> 00:17:35,512
I tried to prolong the trial.

226
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:39,308
Desk is also pursuing it regardless of the danger⸺

227
00:17:39,808 --> 00:17:42,436
I have to make up my mind too.

228
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:44,772
Because I thought so

229
00:17:45,939 --> 00:17:49,276
After all, I was trying to keep it all to myself.

230
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:55,115
but…

231
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:02,915
Toba-chan is not alone now.

232
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:06,251
Dragon…

233
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:08,170
(Rie) Yes.

234
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:10,506
And also about future trial strategies⸺

235
00:18:10,589 --> 00:18:11,882
You can reconsider

236
00:18:11,965 --> 00:18:15,344
Yeah, well, even though it's a strategy, I also rejected the settlement⸺

237
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:17,262
As for what you can do...

238
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:18,180
home

239
00:18:18,263 --> 00:18:20,641
There's one thing I want to confirm.

240
00:18:38,158 --> 00:18:43,580
Stealing recordings isn't just a nerd's exclusive patent, right?

241
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:48,544
(Recorded voice: Kotaro) Hello, you're Kamino-san, right?

242
00:18:50,003 --> 00:18:53,215
The conversation when you called Kotaro-sensei was⸺

243
00:18:53,298 --> 00:18:54,716
everything is recorded

244
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:59,221
Nana... What are you talking about?

245
00:18:59,304 --> 00:19:04,726
If you have this evidence, you can be charged with forcible obstruction of business.

246
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:05,936
Accusation...

247
00:19:06,019 --> 00:19:08,438
(Tatsumi) About trying to trap Kotaro-sensei⸺

248
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:11,859
If you admit it, I won't press charges.

249
00:19:11,942 --> 00:19:13,527
however…

250
00:19:15,946 --> 00:19:18,490
Let me tell you the story

251
00:19:19,074 --> 00:19:22,119
Ha ha ha...

252
00:19:27,165 --> 00:19:32,838
(Recorded voice: Kotaro) Hello, you're Kamino-san, right?

253
